 nationalism more generally.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAsian Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSecurity Studies.  athird parties in civil war/ethnic conflict, success/failure of secessionism, why states/countries don’t allow secession, Secessionist wars.2 aKnowledge Unlatchedefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501713958?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501713958423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501713958/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles